	And not only that, there will be ongoing -- there will be ongoing reviews by anything that is brought to the attention of the career professionals.

	But I just have to go back, Senator, and try to set the record straight. [Clinton Global Initiative] is not in the memorandum of understanding because they already have a practice of disclosing all of their contributions. There is no need to require it.

	I will certainly state here that they're going to continue the practice which they've already done.


